        "title": "How to identify xpath for an element which does not have any tag?",
        "body": "<p>I would need to identify one element uniquely.However that element does not have any tag.Could you please help to identify the element uniquely?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;div class=\"mbs2_support ng-binding\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer care? &lt;/strong&gt;Phone 999 888 777 6&lt;/div&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Here I need to identify only phone number column without \"Customer care\" section.\nHighlighted one(attached screenshot) I need identify.I have tried following xpath, but it is taking whole row(including customer column)<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>//div[contains(text(), ' Phone 999 888 777 6')]<\/code><\/li>\n<li><code>//div[text()[normalize-space()='Phone 999 888 777 6']]<\/code><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pVWv1.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pVWv1.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 51702742,
