        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Vxi1i.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 5764092,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4549554,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4549554/andersson",
                "reputation": 52816,
                "display_name": "Andersson",
                "accept_rate": 59
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533541725,
            "creation_date": 1533541725,
            "body": "<p><em>\"...element does not have any tag\"<\/em> is not actually correct. Required text node is a child of <code>div<\/code>. You can get it with below JavaScript (using <a href=\"https://www.softwaretestingmaterial.com/javascriptexecutor-selenium-webdriver/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JavaScriptExecutor<\/a>):<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>'return document.querySelector(\"div.mbs2_support\").lastChild.textContent;'\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702860,
            "question_id": 51702742
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/957956ce51706d03f19a4dc85a767bb1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1020072,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1030675,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1030675/choroba",
                "reputation": 244895,
                "display_name": "choroba"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533541615,
            "creation_date": 1533541615,
            "body": "<p>Just extract the text() <em>child<\/em> of the diff, the text in <code>&lt;strong&gt;<\/code> is a grandchild, so won't be included:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>//div[contains(., 'Phone ')]/text()\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702834,
            "question_id": 51702742
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/w4d7E.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 10049107,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7429447,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7429447/undetected-selenium",
                "reputation": 194452,
                "display_name": "undetected Selenium",
                "accept_rate": 86
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533551122,
            "creation_date": 1533551122,
            "body": "<p>The element you are trying to identify is a child <code>text Node<\/code> of the parent <code>&lt;div&gt;<\/code> tag.<\/p>\n\n<p>As per the <em>HTML<\/em> you have provided to extract the text <strong>Phone 999 888 777 6<\/strong> you can use the <a href=\"https://seleniumhq.github.io/selenium/docs/api/java/org/openqa/selenium/JavascriptExecutor.html#executeScript-java.lang.String-java.lang.Object...-\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><strong><code>executeScript()<\/code><\/strong><\/a> method as follows:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>WebElement myElement = driver.findElement(By.xpath(\"//div[@class='mbs2_support ng-binding']\"));\nString myText = ((JavascriptExecutor)driver).executeScript('return arguments[0].lastChild.textContent;', myElement).toString();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51705494,
            "question_id": 51702742
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/ip85Y.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 5319472,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4243319,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4243319/anshul-gupta",
                "reputation": 1280,
                "display_name": "anshul Gupta"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533551404,
            "creation_date": 1533551404,
            "body": "<pre><code>WebElement element = driver.findElement(By.xpath(\"//div[contains(@class,'mbs2_support')]\")); \nString getText = ((JavascriptExecutor)driver).executeScript('return arguments[0].lastChild.textContent;', element).toString();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Get the element and parse the string. lastChild in javascript will do the trick: <a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/prop_node_lastchild.asp\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/prop_node_lastchild.asp<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 51705589,
            "question_id": 51702742
        }
